# Pre-commit QA build (mandatory)

Before **any** `git commit`, ALWAYS run a full QA build and confirm it passes. No exceptions.

## Required command

```bash
npx tsc --noEmit && npm run build
```

`npm run build` matches the Vercel production build (`scripts/vercel-bundle/build.mjs && next build`).

## Rules

1. Run QA build **after** code changes are complete and **before** `git add` / `git commit`.
2. If QA build fails — fix errors first; do **not** commit.
3. Do not skip QA build because changes look small or "docs only" (unless the commit is truly git-only with zero file changes).
4. Report build result to the user when committing (pass/fail, or that it was run).

## Optional (when relevant)

After a passing QA build, run targeted smokes if the change touches that area (e.g. `npm run smoke:route-truth`). QA build remains the hard gate; smokes are additive.
